    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1896-10-02T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1896-10-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="595"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d595">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Rockhill</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Taylor</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1896-10-02">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 2, 1896</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 581.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to the Department’s No. 576, of the
                    24th ultimo, so far as it relates to the claim of Messrs. Bauriedel &amp; Co.,
                    agents of certain American tobacco importing houses, to be allowed to export
                    from Cuba tobacco purchased before the date of the Governor-General’s
                    prohibitory decrees, I now inclose copy of a later dispatch<note n="1"
                        xml:id="d595fn1">Not printed.</note> from our consul-general at Habana
                    transmitting the evidence furnished by the claimants to prove their case.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">W. W. Rockhill</hi>,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
